# Hardware & OS Optimization Rules

## 1. Thread Management
- For heavy tasks (AST scanning, Puppeteer work, or environment recovery), offload where practical (e.g. Node **`worker_threads`**) so the Electron UI stays near **60fps**.
- Avoid long synchronous I/O on the main thread during dashboard interactions.

## 2. Windows 11 I/O & pathing
- **Batching:** Batch file operations during **`npm run vpe:nuke-install`**, vault reconcile, or large repairs to reduce Windows Defender overhead.
- **Pathing:** Use the Node **`path`** module; prefer normalized absolute paths on Windows.

## 3. Process safety
- Use **`tree-kill`** (or equivalent) so PM2 / dev child processes are fully reaped.
- **Environment nuke:** The supported sequence matches **`Project-Bible.md` §7**: stop stray **`node.exe`** (**`taskkill /F /IM node.exe /T`**), then run **`npm run vpe:nuke-install`** (includes purge + **`npm install`**). Verify termination before manual directory deletes if you bypass the script.
